Definition of Recycled Plastics
Recycled plastics refer to plastic materials that have been collected, processed, and transformed into new products after their initial use. This process involves several stages, including the collection of plastic waste, sorting, cleaning, and reprocessing it into raw materials. The recycling of plastics is a critical component of waste management and environmental sustainability, aimed at reducing plastic pollution and conserving natural resources. Recycled plastics can be utilized in various applications, including packaging, automotive parts, textiles, and construction materials.
